{"TopicId":50105,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Science: Sun Orbit","CreatedByName":"Sirrobert","CreatedById":70591,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T21:57:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sirrobert","CreatedById":70591,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T21:57:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhat is concidered \u0027low\u0027 orbit for the sun by science parts?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI want to send a probe to low sun orbit to do science there, but where is the threshold?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SRV Ron","CreatedById":69806,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T22:42:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EJust so you don\u0027t get below 1,500 meters or the probe will go POOF! \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mlb1m7J.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022mlb1m7J.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"andrewas","CreatedById":24662,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T22:43:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI think low orbit is below a million meters.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T23:09:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI also believe 1000km is where the changeover from \u0022high above the sun\u0022 switches to \u0022space near the sun.\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T23:14:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYes, million metres.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sirrobert","CreatedById":70591,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T23:26:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThanks guys.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}